text: God's eternal attributes are his essence.
The human nature and divine nature of Jesus are distinct.
The essence of God is distinct from human essence.
The Father has the Hyposthesis, which is a person.
The Father, Son and Holy Spirit are one in essence.
Malachi six-three says God does not change in nature.
Jesus demonstrated a posture of prayer by putting his forehead on the ground.
The nature of Christ is to his personhood.
